metadata.description: Demo-optimized dataset with clear, verifiable answers based on actual RAG data
optimizations: Questions use real provider names and locations
All questions have clear answers in RAG data

questions.question: What is the copay for a primary care visit on the Platinum PPO plan?
questions.expected_answer: The copay for a primary care visit on the Platinum PPO plan is $20.

questions.question: Can you help me find a dermatologist in New York who accepts the Platinum PPO plan?
questions.expected_answer: Provider recommendations including Dr. William B. Cohen at New York Dermatology Center

questions.question: Does the Gold HMO plan require referrals for specialist visits?
questions.expected_answer: Yes, the Gold HMO plan requires referrals from your primary care physician for specialist visits.

questions.question: What is the copay for generic medications on the Platinum PPO plan?
questions.expected_answer: Generic (Tier 1) medications cost $5 for a 30-day retail supply and $10 for a 90-day mail order supply on the Platinum PPO plan.

questions.question: I need a primary care doctor in San Francisco. What providers are available?
questions.expected_answer: Provider recommendations including Dr. Kevin B. Patel at San Francisco Internal Medicine

questions.question: Tell me about the Diabetes Management Program for Platinum PPO members.
questions.expected_answer: Platinum PPO members get free glucose monitor, unlimited test strips, and 12 nutritionist sessions per year at no cost, plus quarterly care coordinator check-ins.

questions.question: What is the emergency room copay for the Platinum PPO plan?
questions.expected_answer: The emergency room copay for the Platinum PPO plan is $250.

questions.question: Are there any mental health providers in Seattle who accept my plan?
questions.expected_answer: Mental health providers in Seattle including specific provider names and locations

questions.question: Does the Gold HMO plan cover out-of-network providers?
questions.expected_answer: No, the Gold HMO plan only covers in-network providers except for emergency services.

questions.question: What is the specialist visit copay on the Platinum PPO plan?
questions.expected_answer: The specialist visit copay on the Platinum PPO plan is $35.

questions.question: I'm looking for an internal medicine doctor in San Francisco.
questions.expected_answer: Provider recommendations including Dr. Kevin B. Patel, Internal Medicine specialist

questions.question: How many nutritionist visits do Gold HMO members get through the Diabetes Management Program?
questions.expected_answer: Gold HMO members get 6 nutritionist sessions per year at no cost through the Diabetes Management Program.

questions.question: What is the urgent care copay for Platinum PPO?
questions.expected_answer: The urgent care copay for Platinum PPO is $50.

questions.question: Can you find me a pharmacy in Portland, Oregon?
questions.expected_answer: Pharmacy locations in Portland, Oregon

questions.question: What are the key features of the Gold HMO plan?
questions.expected_answer: Gold HMO requires a PCP, requires referrals for specialists, in-network only coverage, coordinated care model, and lower out-of-pocket costs.

questions.question: What is the mail order copay for preferred brand drugs on Platinum PPO?
questions.expected_answer: Preferred brand (Tier 2) medications cost $50 for a 90-day mail order supply on Platinum PPO.

questions.question: I need to find a specialist in Texas. What's available?
questions.expected_answer: Specialist providers in various Texas cities (Houston, Dallas, Austin)

questions.question: Does the Platinum PPO require a primary care physician?
questions.expected_answer: No, the Platinum PPO does not require selecting a primary care physician, and you don't need referrals for specialists.

questions.question: What networks does Dr. Kevin Patel participate in?
questions.expected_answer: Dr. Kevin B. Patel participates in TH-EPO-SELECT, TH-HMO-PRIMARY, and TH-PPO-PREMIER networks.

questions.question: What is the specialty drug copay for Platinum PPO at retail?
questions.expected_answer: Specialty (Tier 4) medications cost $100 for a 30-day retail supply on Platinum PPO. They are not available by mail order.

questions.question: Find me a primary care doctor in Boston.
questions.expected_answer: Primary care providers in Boston/Massachusetts area

questions.question: Which ToggleHealth plans are eligible for the Diabetes Management Program?
questions.expected_answer: All ToggleHealth plans are eligible: Gold HMO, Platinum PPO, Silver EPO, and Bronze HDHP.

questions.question: I'm looking for mental health services in Chicago.
questions.expected_answer: Mental health providers in Chicago/Illinois area

questions.question: What is the contact number for the Pacific Northwest Diabetes Center?
questions.expected_answer: The Pacific Northwest Diabetes Center can be reached at 206-555-8001.

questions.question: Show me dermatologists in California who accept Silver EPO.
questions.expected_answer: Dermatology specialists in California cities accepting Silver EPO plan

questions.question: Does the Diabetes Management Program cover glucose monitors for Silver EPO members?
questions.expected_answer: Yes, Silver EPO members get discounted glucose monitors and test strips through the Diabetes Management Program.

questions.question: Can you recommend a pharmacy in Phoenix?
questions.expected_answer: Pharmacy locations in Phoenix, Arizona

questions.question: What is the address of the Pacific Northwest Diabetes Center?
questions.expected_answer: The Pacific Northwest Diabetes Center is located at 3500 Endocrine Way, Seattle, WA 98109.

questions.question: I need a specialist in Denver, Colorado.
questions.expected_answer: Specialist providers in Denver, Colorado area

questions.question: How do I enroll in the Diabetes Management Program?
questions.expected_answer: You can enroll by calling Member Services at 1-800-TOGGLE-1, having your doctor submit a referral, or members with diabetes diagnosis codes are automatically enrolled.

questions.question: Find primary care doctors in Washington state.
questions.expected_answer: Primary care providers in Washington state (Seattle area)

questions.question: Do copays apply before the deductible is met on Platinum PPO?
questions.expected_answer: Yes, copays apply even before the deductible is met on Platinum PPO. After copay, the plan pays 90% of additional costs after deductible.

questions.question: Are there any specialists in Atlanta accepting new patients?
questions.expected_answer: Specialist providers in Atlanta, Georgia area accepting new patients

questions.question: What services does the Pacific Northwest Diabetes Center provide?
questions.expected_answer: The center provides diabetes education, insulin pump training, continuous glucose monitoring, endocrinology consultations, nutrition counseling, and diabetes foot care.

questions.question: I'm looking for a doctor in New York who accepts Gold HMO.
questions.expected_answer: Providers in New York accepting Gold HMO plan

questions.question: Are specialty medications available by mail order on Platinum PPO?
questions.expected_answer: No, specialty (Tier 4) medications are not available by mail order on Platinum PPO.

questions.question: Show me pharmacies in Washington, DC.
questions.expected_answer: Pharmacy locations in Washington, DC area

questions.question: What diabetes education services are covered at 100%?
questions.expected_answer: Accredited diabetes self-management education classes are covered at 100% regardless of deductible for all Diabetes Management Program members.

questions.question: I need a mental health provider in Pennsylvania.
questions.expected_answer: Mental health providers in Pennsylvania (Philadelphia area)

questions.question: What is Dr. William Cohen's specialty?
questions.expected_answer: Dr. William B. Cohen is a Dermatology specialist at New York Dermatology Center.

questions.question: Can Bronze HDHP members get free glucose monitors through the Diabetes Program?
questions.expected_answer: No, glucose monitors and nutritionist visits are subject to the deductible for Bronze HDHP members in the Diabetes Management Program.

questions.question: Find me doctors in Florida who accept the Silver EPO plan.
questions.expected_answer: Providers in Florida accepting Silver EPO plan

questions.question: What prescription drug tiers does Platinum PPO have?
questions.expected_answer: Platinum PPO has four tiers: Generic (Tier 1), Preferred Brand (Tier 2), Non-Preferred Brand (Tier 3), and Specialty (Tier 4).

questions.question: Are there any primary care doctors in Minneapolis?
questions.expected_answer: Primary care providers in Minneapolis, Minnesota area

questions.question: How many years has Dr. Kevin Patel been in practice?
questions.expected_answer: Dr. Kevin B. Patel has been in practice for 13 years.

questions.question: What is the retail copay for non-preferred brand drugs on Platinum PPO?
questions.expected_answer: Non-preferred brand (Tier 3) medications cost $50 for a 30-day retail supply on Platinum PPO.

questions.question: Show me specialists in North Carolina.
questions.expected_answer: Specialist providers in North Carolina

questions.question: What plans does Dr. William Cohen accept?
questions.expected_answer: Dr. William B. Cohen accepts TH-EPO-SILVER-2024 and TH-PPO-PLATINUM-2024.

questions.question: Is Dr. Kevin Patel accepting new patients?
questions.expected_answer: Yes, Dr. Kevin B. Patel is accepting new patients.

questions.question: What is Dr. William Cohen's patient rating?
questions.expected_answer: Dr. William B. Cohen has an average rating of 4.9/5.0 based on 407 total reviews.
